message: Can anybody tell me how a website like www.eventtus.com make money?
story: Muhammad El-Hennawy shared a link to the group: Egyptian Geeks.
name: Eventtus: Socialize your event with the best networking app & platform
caption: eventtus.com
description: Boost your event and give your attendees the best experience they will ever have. Interactive agenda, rich speaker profiles, real time polls and more.

data.message: From this, I would say B2B. They provide big events/organizers with a service to manage their event schedule for the attendees through the app.

Just know that Meetup's story and how much it was struggling to monetize its business. Meetup ended to charge the event organizers and put a strict curation rules to guarantee the quality of the platform. I understand that many businesses want to capitalize Millennials who are mostly would spend more on got experiences through events and travel, because they are mostly can't afford to own properties or assets. But, I don't really know how sustainable eventtus business model is ?!

1. http://eventtus.com/pricing so they charge event organisers for premium features.
2. percentage from all the sold ticket through the website.
3. B2B (deals) as Mohamed said
Actually they started by taking percentage from ticket price .. then they started the event managing feature like whova.com
Thank you Ahmed Salah that is really helpful, I am still really wonder how this app is financially sound in Egypt?!

this app specifically power came from the support of their investors .. vodafone .. using vodafone cash as one of their payment methods make make them rock stars against ticketmarch for example .. this is all happens before the evolution of fawry and payfort off course .. according to numbers and current state of the startup it should be good as they opened recently a new market at dubai
They have a tab called Pricing, have you checked it yet!!
Took 10% of tickets purchasing and selling premium packages with different features
